The paper proposes a technique for temporal information extraction from text using LSTM-based models. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically, information extraction. The paper also mentions the use of syntactic dependencies, which suggests a focus on parsing and syntax. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and computational linguistics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as these also cover topics related to NLP and machine learning.
